    "created_at": "2017-01-24T18:48:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-01-24T18:48:03Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "However, there is probably no small fix for this at the moment. Without doing periodic health checks, there is no way for the client to know that its connection with the original server is no longer good. It needs that first failure to go through the process of remaking the connection.\r\n\r\nGood news is that this will be fix once retry support is integrated in to the c core. That is an ongoing project and will be accomplished within the next three months"
  },
